track_notes: Short but fairly steep hike to the summit of Pemetic. Nice view of Jordan pond as well as Cadilac Mt.

On a warm day, in the vacation season, parking is a major problem in Acadia Park. All the parking areas close to this summit were spilling over. The nearest  parking, I could find, was on route 3, about a mile east of Seal Harbor. This leaves a 4 mile hike to the top of Permetic Mountain. Fortunately, about 3 miles of the trek is on Carriage Roads, which makes for easy walking. The last mile gets serious. See attached route.
track_title: Route up Permetic Mountain from the south.

track_notes: This is a short but steep trail. Staring from the Bubbles parking area, cross the road, to the East, and start climbing.
track_title: Route up Permetic Mtn, from the West.
